Spicy and saucy paneer 65 recipe 🤤🍃

Ingredients for paneer 65 recipe:
Paneer 250 gram

Mustard seed 1/2 tsp

Green chilli 2-3 
Onion 2 medium size (1/2 finely chopped)

Coriander powder 1/2 tsp 
Garam masala 1/2 tsp 
Ginger garlic paste 1 tsp 
Salt 
(Gently mix and coat well)

latestPosts.caption:
Stuffed schezwan garlic bread recipe 🤤🌶️
Do try it and save for later 🙌🏻

Ingredients for schezwan garlic bread recipe:
Sandwich Bread slices 
Butter 2 big tsp 
Minced garlic 10-12 cloves 
Oregano 1 tsp 
Chilli flakes 1/2 tsp
Green chilli 2 finely chopped 
Coriander 1 tsp 
Schezwan chutney 1 big tsp 

For stuffing ingredients:
Grated mozzarella cheese 1/2 cup 
Sweet corn 1-2 tsp 
Paneer cubes 100 gram 
Oregano and chilli flakes 

Instructions:
Step1: In a bowl add 2 tsp butter, minced garlic 1 tsp, oregano 1 tsp, chilli flakes 1/2 tsp, green chilli 1, coriander 1 tsp and schezwan chutney 1 big tsp (mix well until combined) 

Step2: take a sandwich bread cut the bread slices into circle and gently roll and make it flat spread schezwan garlic butter 

Step3: add grated cheese, sweet corn, paneer cubes sprinkle oregano and chilli flakes (fold half) 

Step4: cover and cook for 3-4mins on low flame (toast both sides)

Serve and enjoy! ☺️

Quick & easy paneer burger recipe 🤤🍔
Do try it and save for later 🙌🏻

Ingredients for paneer burger recipe:
Oil for frying 
Paneer slices 2-3 
Corn flour 2 big tsp 
Refined flour 2 tsp 
Ginger garlic paste 1 tsp 
Oregano 1 tsp 
Chilli flakes 1/3 tsp 
Salt 1/3 tsp 
Mayonnaise 2 tsp 
Tomato sauce 2 tsp 
Chilli sauce 1 tsp 
Onion slices 
Cucumber slices 
Tomato slices 
Chat masala 
Bread crumbs 

Instructions:
Step1: Prepare slurry by combining corn flour 2 tsp, refined flour 2 tsp, Ginger garlic paste 1 tsp oregano1 tsp, chilli flakes 1/3 tsp salt and water to form a flowing slurry 

Step2: dip paneer slices in prepared slurry and coat with bread crumbs 

Step3: rest the coated paneer for 15mins and shallow fry 

Step4: In a small bowl mix mayonnaise 2 tsp, tomato sauce 2 tsp and chilli sauce 

Step5: assemble paneer burger and enjoy!

Crispy paneer cutlets recipe 🤤🍃
Do try it and save for later 🙌🏻

Ingredients for paneer cutlets:
Oil 2 tsp (and for frying)
Paneer 250 gram grated 
Cumin seeds 1/2 tbsp 
Green chilli 2 
Ginger 1 inch chopped 
Onion 1 medium size 
Capsicum 1/2 medium size 
Carrot 1 medium size finely chopped 
Garam masala 1/2 tsp 
Coriander powder 1/2 tsp 
Turmeric powder 1/4 tsp 
Amchur powder 1/2 tsp 
Salt 1/2 tsp 
Bread crumbs 
Coriander chopped 2 big tbsp 

Ingredients for slurry:
Refined flour (maida) 1/2 cup 
Corn flour 1/2 cup 
Chilli powder 1/3 tsp 
Salt 1/3 tsp 
Water (gradually add water to form flowing consistency slurry)

Instructions:
Step1: In a bowl combine grated paneer, veggies, coriander and mix well (if the mixture is moist add 1 cup bread crumbs)

Step2: prepare slurry by combining 1/2 cup refined flour, 1/2 cup corn flour, chilli powder, salt and water 

Step3: prepare a small size tikki din in prepared slurry and coat with bread crumbs 

Step4: deep fry in hot oil on medium flame serve with coriander chutney and enjoy ☺️

Ingredients for vermicelli upma recipe:
Ghee 2 big tbsp 
Vermicelli 2 cups small 
Roasted Peanut 2-3 tbsp 
Mustard seeds 1/2 tbsp 
Cumin seeds 1/2 tbsp 
Urad dal 1 tbsp 
Chana dal 1 tbsp 
Cashews 8-10
Ginger 1/2 inch 
Green chilli 2 
Curry leaves 10-12 
Onion 1 medium size 
Peas 1/2 cups 
Carrot 1 medium size 
Capsicum 1 medium size 
Tomato 1 medium size 
Turmeric powder 1/4 tbsp 
Salt 1 tbsp 
Lemon juice 1-2 tbsp 
Coriander chopped 

Instructions:
Step1: in a deep pan boil water add 2 cups vermicelli and salt 1/2 tbsp and boil for 4-5 mins 

Step2: strain off water and allow to cool completely 

Step3: for roasted peanut heat a pan add 2-3 tbsp peanut and roast for 4-5 mins on medium to low flame
